description.narrative:
In consultation and coordination with UNOCHA, RRC, and WASH and FSL clusters, Cordaid will target the most vulnerable households, who are in IPC4+. Besides this, other criteria that will be considered include:  
•	Female headed households;
•	Child headed households;
•	Elderly headed households;
•	Households with persons with specific needs (PSN) including chronically ill, PWD, PLW;
•	Households with no basic items /or those who have lost most of their properties;
•	Households without income/livelihood opportunities

comment.narrative:
Mazabuka District Sustainable Landscape Management Programme Multi-Stakeholder Platform continued;
Partnerships with Kasisi and WARMA/ continued 
Dialogues include technical working groups, of which four have been established in 2018
